  "prompt": "Will data used between 2am -5am be debited from Jio data plan or is it separately taken care of?",
  "response": "For Jio data plans, there isn't a specific restriction or separate allocation for data usage between 2 AM to 5 AM. Data used during this period is generally considered part of your total data allowance for the plan you have subscribed to. If you are using a plan that includes a certain amount of data, all usage, regardless of the time, will be deducted from that allowance.\n\nHowever, Jio has previously offered unlimited data at certain times for specific plans or promotions, but these would depend on the terms of that particular offer. Always check the details of your specific plan and any promotions that may apply to ensure you have the most accurate and updated information.",
